          <Comment>For these reasons, this variant has been classified as Pathogenic. This variant has not been reported in the literature in individuals affected with SLX4-related conditions. This variant is not present in population databases (gnomAD no frequency). This sequence change creates a premature translational stop signal (p.Ser1342Alafs*33) in the SLX4 gene. It is expected to result in an absent or disrupted protein product. Loss-of-function variants in SLX4 are known to be pathogenic (PMID: 21240277).</Comment>
